    {
      "id": "p002",
      "index": 2,
      "source": "Our datacenter CPU roadmap features 9 companies over 12 years from 2017 to 2028 including AMD, Intel, Nvidia, Ampere, AWS, Google, Microsoft, ARM and Huawei. The roadmap for clients also feature Qualcomm’s datacenter CPUs. With the acquisition, Ampere Computing’s lineup will be changed to try to intersect with OpenAI.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0274",
      "parent_block_index": 274,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "Our datacenter CPU roadmap features 9 companies over 12 years from 2017 to 2028 including AMD, Intel, Nvidia, Ampere, AWS, Google, Microsoft, ARM and Huawei. The roadmap for clients also feature Qualcomm’s datacenter CPUs. With the acquisition, Ampere Computing’s lineup will be changed to try to intersect with OpenAI.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "Our datacenter CPU roadmap features 9 companies over 12 years from 2017 to 2028 including AMD, Intel, Nvidia, Ampere, AWS, Google, Microsoft, ARM and Huawei. The roadmap for clients also feature Qualcomm’s datacenter CPUs. With the acquisition, Ampere Computing’s lineup will be changed to try to intersect with OpenAI.",
